general.description: Created for longer trips or full-time living, the Classic Travel Trailer offers every comfort of home you want - plus plenty of amenities you didn't even know you needed. Hit the road knowing you'll start and end each day surrounded in features that transform a road trip into a true getaway.

features: Take a closer look at the Classic, both inside and out. See the design, storage, appliances, and technology that make the Classic feel as spacious and elegant as home.

In the Classic 33FB floor plan you get a dedicated living and lounging area with a projection entertainment system. The 60'' screen lowers from the upper cabinet with the touch of a button on the remote, and is perfectly located across from the reclining sofa. Turn on cinema mode to dim the lights, lower the shades, activate the Bose(r) sound bar, and have the ultimate movie night experience.

The Classic 33FB bathroom feels nothing like an RV bathroom. It's a spacious, three-piece residential-style layout, with a large shower and a mirrored double-door wardrobe that makes getting ready a true pleasure. It also includes a heated shower floor to warm you up as soon as you step inside, and a heated towel bar to keep you warm when you step out. It's those little things that completely change your morning, or your whole day.
Powered Beds Adjust to sit or sleep more elevated, lie flat, or rest somewhere in between. The powered bed lets you choose your perfect sleep, with controls located right beside the bed.
Quietstream(tm) Climate Control Our ducted air conditioning system easily and quickly cools the cabin in relative silence. It even features a heat pump to pull ambient heat from the air.
Doorbell It's the little touches that really make a travel trailer feel like home. The LED doorbell at the entrance of the Classic is a bonus your guests will love.
Power Awning A power awning comes standard, opens with the push of a button, and is sure to be one of the features you use the most.

Premium Audio Experience The Fusion touchscreen stereo includes Wi-Fi, Apple AirPlay & Bluetooth(r) connectivity, over-the-air software updates, SiriusXM, and can be controlled from the Fusion mobile app.
Rear-view Monitoring A rear-view camera is mounted to the back of the trailer to make backing up and parking so much easier.
Comfort White with Earl Grey Ultraleather(r)

Shaker-style cabinets made from imported European Beech wood in a white finish. Accented with contemporary, German imported, brass hardware, the knobs and pulls add an element of refinement. Contrasting the white cabinets, dark counters bring a sophistication and warmth to the space.

features: Take a closer look at the Globetrotter, both inside and out. See the design choices, technology, and modern appliances that make the Globetrotter feel like it was made just for you.

A major part of the Globetrotter(r) Travel Trailer's appeal is how seamless the storage feels. Upper storage cabinets throughout the travel trailer are finished with our custom curved wood doors, coated in a bright white that's resistant to fingerprints. Inside are hydraulic hinges that keep the doors in place when they're fully open and add a soft close when you pull them shut.

The kitchen and bathroom of the Globetrotter both feature Corian countertops with a modern blunt edge that follows the lines of the cabinetry below. The bright white color helps light bounce off of the Airstream aluminum walls and matches the white lockers above. Plus, there are built-in counter features, like two multifunctional storage bins that rest flush with the surface behind the sink.
Modern and Practical Kitchen The kitchen is as beautiful as it is useful. Prepare healthy meals for the family with all of the premium appliances you would expect to see in a residential kitchen.
Quietstream(tm) Climate Control Our ducted air conditioning system easily and quickly cools the cabin in relative silence. It even features a heat pump to pull ambient heat from the air.
Cast Aluminum Tail Lights LED tail lights in round dual ovals harken back to 60s modern style.
Rear-view Monitoring A rear-view camera is mounted to the back of the trailer to make backing up and parking so much easier.
USB and 110V Outlets USB ports and 110V outlets are strategically placed around the trailer, so you never have to go far to keep your devices charged and ready.
Solar Package with Interior Monitor + Pre-wire Kit Solar panels extend the amount of time you can stay powered up off the grid.

London Grey seating and light cabinetry create a bright, open interior.

general.description: The Flying Cloud is our most popular, versatile, and family-friendly travel trailer. With more floor plans available than any other model, there's a "just right" for everyone. And the light and airy design keeps you ready to float from one adventure to the next, bringing your comfort zone right along with you.

features: Air conditioning and heating can make or break a trip. That's why our Quietstream ducted climate control system easily and quickly cools the cabin, and does so in relative silence. It even features a heat pump that pulls ambient heat from the air to warm the travel trailer without using the furnace - and without causing condensation. And when you really need to warm up, the onboard furnace is ready for cold-weather trips, too.

At Airstream, every single design choice is made for a reason. And in fact, there are plenty of reasons we use Ultraleather for our travel trailer furniture. It's incredibly supple and soft, yet durable and long-lasting with special strengthening components. It resists temperature change and will never crack from cold weather. And it's easy to clean, pet-friendly, and won't scratch or stain, so your furniture looks as beautiful on day one as it does long down the road.
Memory Foam Mattress Each bed features a pillow top memory foam mattress for a great night's sleep in between adventures.
Handcrafted Cabinetry Each cabinet is made of high-quality materials that stand the test of time while keeping your trailer light on its feet.
Retractable Awning The durable and beautiful ZipDee(r) awning with Sunbrella(tm) fabric is sure to be one of the features you use the most.
Rear-view Monitoring System A rear-view camera is mounted to the back of the trailer to make backing up and parking so much easier.
Roller Blinds and Blackout Curtains Oceanair blinds throughout the trailer easily roll open or closed, while blackout curtains in the front and back provide complete privacy.
Moen(r) Galley Faucets Sleek Delta faucets bring the modern design and convenience you love at home along for the journey.

features: Did you know you can roast a chicken in a convection microwave? That's just one of the available Caravel kitchen features that'll inspire a more exciting camp meal. From the stainless steel gas stove with cast-iron burners to the modern residential Moen(r) faucet, you'll enjoy cooking even more in a space you love to use.

It's all about the view, and no matter which side of the Caravel 16RB you're on you've got a panoramic one. Our hand-crafted, custom Airstream windows are riveted right into the frame of the travel trailer and designed to give you a bigger opening radius so more breeze can flow throughout the cabin.
Front and Window Awnings The performance Sunbrella(r) pinstripe front awning provides shaded outdoor space, and the optional matching window awnings keep the interior cool and private.
Rear Bumper Storage Store your tools, cords, and more into bonus space in the rear bumper.

Solar Power Solar panels extend the amount of time you can stay powered up off the grid.
Roller Shades and Blackout Curtains Pull down the shades and close the blackout curtains when you're headed to bed, when you want more privacy, or when you just want to keep the trailer extra cool.
Stainless Steel Rock Guards The Caravel features the same stainless steel rock guards we use on our larger travel trailers to prevent damage to the body of your trailer during towing.
Stacked Double Tail Lights Drivers behind the Caravel will know it's a special travel trailer with these modern yet retro double cast aluminum tail lights.
All-Electric Refrigerator The refrigerator runs off of battery power, which helps it get cold quickly and efficiently, and stay cool throughout your trip.
Power Tongue Jack Makes hitching and unhitching easier and more accessible for everyone.

features: Basecamp(r) is made of the same riveted aluminum superstructure as our traditional travel trailers, yet it introduces a new shape to the family. Its aerodynamic body and roof profile slip through the air on the open road and help increase fuel efficiency. And the panoramic front windows let you take in the world around you - the whole reason you head out to explore in the first place. Get the Quality Guide

Every adventurer needs a place to recharge and Basecamp doesn't overlook comfort for a second. When you're setting up camp somewhere hot, the optional air conditioning with two-speed fan will keep you cool. When you're surrounded by snow, the onboard furnace and hot water heater system(s) will warm things up with world-class efficiency.

Quickly and smoothly expand Basecamp's living and storage space with an inflatable tube frame tent attachment. With two entry points and two rooms, the tent's versatility makes it easier to grab your gear and go or set up camp and relax for the day.
Removable Tables Two tables make the perfect surface for entertaining, eating, and working. And when you want more room to move around, quickly stow them away.
Outdoor Shower Use the pass-through in the bathroom wall to create an outdoor shower for your gear or yourself.
Flexible Living Space Choose between 7 different bench configurations to fit your needs. With a half-bed, full bed, or seating for up to five, there are plenty of options.
Remote Work Station With a convertible table and USB ports/110V outlets all around, you can keep your devices charged on the road.
Spradling Marine Fabric Basecamp seating is covered in antibacterial, mildew-resistant, stain-resistant, and flame-retardant fabric for lasting durability.
Easy Access Load and unload larger gear that otherwise would be difficult to get through the main entry door.

general.description: The Atlas Touring Coach is our most luxurious touring coach to date. It's a Class B+ RV built on the legendary Mercedes-Benz(r) Sprinter van chassis and inspired by our trailblazing Airstream Interstate series. In fact, with its power slide-out, richly appointed features and finishes, and understated automotive styling from grill to bumper, we affectionately call it a Class B+. A new standard has arrived for those who believe a well-traveled life begins with the best.

features: If you can't imagine a day without your creature comforts, you'll be right at home in the Atlas(tm). While you're traveling, you have plenty of room for passengers to ride along on the sofa and use the aisle. And when you get settled, you can extend the slide-out and pull down a large Murphy bed for a truly great night's sleep, plus lovely extras like reading lights and shelves for your books and glasses.

Whether you're tailgating, entertaining friends, or just having a movie night, the Atlas' 40" Samsung LED Smart TV with a built-in sound bar is perfect. When you're not using it, it stays tucked inside the entertainment cabinet under the Corian(r) countertop. Then, you simply push a button and it rises into position, right across from the sofa or Murphy bed.
Airstream Connected Ready Roam further while staying connected with a pre-wired Airstream Connected kit. A high performance antenna and all necessary wiring come standard.
Power Armless Awning with Auto-Retract With the tap of a button you can enjoy the perfect amount of shade from the sun. With auto-retract, the awning will automatically close if the wind picks up.
Tankless Water Heater Enjoy continuous hot water in the shower and the galley thanks to an onboard tankless water heater. It heats water more efficiently, and saves valuable space.
Onan(r) Diesel Generator With its own compartment along the wheel-base of the Atlas, the Onan 3.2kw diesel generator provides quiet and efficient power when you're not plugged into electricity.
Dedicated Camera Monitor In the place of a rearview mirror, we've included a dedicated camera monitor for your rear and side cameras. You get an accurate picture of your surroundings at all times.
Auto-retracting Steps Open the cabin door and the steps automatically unfold and extend before you. Close the door and they automatically retract to become flush with the body of the Atlas.
Quietstream(tm) Climate Control Our ducted air conditioning system easily and quickly cools the cabin in relative silence. It even features a heat pump to pull ambient heat from the air.
Froli(r) Ergonomic Sleep System The mattress in the Murphy suite rests on a Froli system of interlocking springs that provides a supportive, ergonomic sleeping surface, just like at home.
Power Sunroof with Screen Inside the main cabin above the sofa is a built-in sunroof with a power shade and screen, so you can get some sunlight, fresh air, or both whenever you like.

features: With a power sofa and side seats that convert into a sleeping space, you get the best of both worlds in the Interstate 19. Relax or catch up on emails on the sofa during the day, then push a button and the sofa becomes completely flat. You can open or close all of the shades in the Interstate 19 with one touch on the C-Zone control screen. The same goes for the interior lighting, the power awning outside, and features like the air conditioning, generator power, and more. You can also monitor tank and power levels with easy digital readouts on the C-Zone screen.

The European-style wet bath in the Interstate 19 neatly houses a sink, shower, and toilet, plus a built-in shampoo, conditioner, and body wash station and a clothesline - everything you need to feel clean and energized on the road. Every inch of the space is designed to get wet, and every function is smart and efficient. The showerhead doubles as the faucet, the mirror extends and swivels, and there's a totally waterproof toilet paper cover.
Rear Camera Monitor In the place of a rearview mirror, we've included a dedicated camera monitor for your rear and side cameras. You get an accurate picture of your surroundings at all times.
Power Exterior Awning An integrated power awning extends via the Multiplex control panel and includes stabilizing bars to help the awning withstand high winds and prevent damage.

Truma Combi Furnace and Water Heater The Truma Combi system combines heating and water heating in one ultra-efficient and space-saving appliance. Because it doesn't use a tank, you can enjoy abundant hot water in the kitchen and bathroom.
Corian(r) Countertops Real Corian countertops give the galley kitchen a sophisticated, residential feel that'll inspire you to whip up something great.
Ultraleather Seating Supple and soft, yet durable and strong. Resists temperature change and is easy to clean, pet-friendly, and won't scratch or stain.
Side and Rear Screen Doors Park for the afternoon or the evening and let the fresh air move throughout the coach, thanks to a sliding side screen and a power rear screen.
Samsung(r) LED HD TV The high-definition widescreen TV is positioned right in front of the rear sofa on an articulating arm that makes it easy to get the perfect angle.
Premium Italian Cabinetry Quality Italian wood is crafted by hand to make a sleek seamless face for all of the Nineteen's storage compartments, from the overhead lockers to the drawers and pantry.
Powered Entry Step & Door The powered side entry door and step automatically work together with the pull of the outside handle or tap of a button from the inside.
